#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:2
msgid "溯源分析"
msgstr "Attribution Analysis"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:5
msgid "攻击机溯源技术"
msgstr "Attacking Host Attribution Techniques"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:8
msgid "基于日志的溯源"
msgstr "Log-Based Attribution"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:9
msgid "使用路由器、主机等设备记录网络传输的数据流中的关键信息(时间、源地址、目的地址)，追踪时基于日志查询做反向追踪。"
msgstr "Use routers, hosts, and other devices to record key information in network traffic flows, such as time, source address, and destination address, and perform reverse tracing through log queries during investigation."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:11
msgid "这种方式的优点在于兼容性强、支持事后追溯、网络开销较小。但是同时该方法也受性能、空间和隐私保护等的限制，考虑到以上的因素，可以限制记录的数据特征和数据数量。另外可以使用流量镜像等技术来减小对网络性能的影响。"
msgstr "This approach has strong compatibility, supports post-incident tracing, and has relatively low network overhead. However, it is also constrained by performance, storage, and privacy protection. Given these factors, the recorded data features and volume can be limited. Traffic mirroring and similar techniques can also reduce the impact on network performance."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:14
msgid "路由输入调试技术"
msgstr "Router Input Debugging"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:15
msgid "在攻击持续发送数据，且特性较为稳定的场景下，可以使用路由器的输入调试技术，在匹配到攻击流量时动态的向上追踪。这种方式在DDoS攻击追溯中比较有效，且网络开销较小。"
msgstr "When an attack continuously sends data and its characteristics are relatively stable, router input debugging can be used to dynamically trace upstream when attack traffic is matched. This method is effective for DDoS attribution and has relatively low network overhead."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:18
msgid "可控洪泛技术"
msgstr "Controlled Flooding"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:19
msgid "追踪时向潜在的上游路由器进行洪泛攻击，如果发现收到的攻击流量变少则攻击流量会流经相应的路由。这种方式的优点在于不需要预先部署，对协同的需求比较少。但是这种方式本身是一种攻击，会对网络有所影响。"
msgstr "During tracing, flood potential upstream routers. If the received attack traffic decreases, the attack traffic is likely passing through the corresponding route. This approach does not require prior deployment and needs less coordination. However, the method itself is an attack and will affect the network."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:22
msgid "基于包数据修改追溯技术"
msgstr "Packet Modification-Based Traceback"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:23
msgid "这种溯源方式直接对数据包进行修改，加入编码或者标记信息，在接收端对传输路径进行重构。这种方式人力投入较少，支持事后分析，但是对某些协议的支持性不太好。"
msgstr "This attribution method directly modifies packets by adding encoded or marking information, then reconstructs the transmission path at the receiver. It requires less manual effort and supports post-incident analysis, but its support for some protocols is limited."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:25
msgid "基于这种方式衍生出了随机标记技术，各路由以一定概率对数据包进行标识，接收端收集到多个包后进行重构。"
msgstr "Random marking techniques are derived from this approach. Each router marks packets with a certain probability, and the receiver reconstructs the path after collecting multiple packets."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:28
msgid "基于蜜罐溯源"
msgstr "Honeypot-Based Attribution"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:29
msgid "社交网络jsonp API"
msgstr "Social network JSONP API"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:30
msgid "获取攻击者IP"
msgstr "Obtain the attacker IP"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:31
msgid "获取burp信息"
msgstr "Obtain Burp information"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:34
msgid "分析模型"
msgstr "Analysis Models"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:37
msgid "杀伤链(Kill Kain)模型"
msgstr "Kill Chain Model"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:38
msgid ""
"杀伤链这个概念源自军事领域，它是一个描述攻击环节的模型。一般杀伤链有认为侦查跟踪(Reconnaissance)、武器构建(Weaponization)、载荷投递(Delivery)、漏洞利用(Exploitation)、安装植入(Installation)、通信控制(Command&Control)、达成目标(Actions"
" on Objective)等几个阶段。"
msgstr ""
"The Kill Chain concept originated in the military domain. It is a model that describes the stages of an attack. A typical kill chain includes stages such as Reconnaissance, Weaponization, Delivery, Exploitation, Installation, Command&Control, and Actions "
"on Objective."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:40
msgid "在越早的杀伤链环节阻止攻击，防护效果就越好，因此杀伤链的概念也可以用来反制攻击。"
msgstr "The earlier an attack is blocked in the kill chain, the better the defensive effect. Therefore, the kill chain concept can also be used to counter attacks."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:42
msgid "在跟踪阶段，攻击者通常会采用扫描和搜索等方式来寻找可能的目标信息并评估攻击成本。在这个阶段可以通过日志分析、邮件分析等方式来发现，这阶段也可以采用威胁情报等方式来获取攻击信息。"
msgstr "In the reconnaissance stage, attackers usually use scanning and search methods to find possible target information and evaluate attack cost. This stage can be detected through log analysis, email analysis, and similar methods, and threat intelligence can also be used to obtain attack information."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:44
msgid "武器构建阶段攻击者通常已经准备好了攻击工具，并进行尝试性的攻击，在这个阶段IDS中可能有攻击记录，外网应用、邮箱等帐号可能有密码爆破的记录。有一些攻击者会使用公开攻击工具，会带有一定的已知特征。"
msgstr "During the weaponization stage, attackers usually have prepared attack tools and may conduct trial attacks. IDS devices may record attacks at this stage, and Internet-facing applications, email accounts, and similar accounts may show password brute-force records. Some attackers use public attack tools that carry known characteristics."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:46
msgid "载荷投递阶段攻击者通常会采用网络漏洞、鱼叉、水坑、网络劫持、U盘等方式投送恶意代码。此阶段已经有人员在对应的途径收到了攻击载荷，对人员进行充分的安全培训可以做到一定程度的防御。"
msgstr "During the delivery stage, attackers usually deliver malicious code through network vulnerabilities, spear phishing, watering-hole attacks, network hijacking, USB drives, and similar methods. At this stage, personnel have already received the payload through the corresponding channel, and sufficient security training can provide some degree of defense."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:48
msgid "突防利用阶段攻击者会执行恶意代码来获取系统控制权限，此时木马程序已经执行，此阶段可以依靠杀毒软件、异常行为告警等方式来找到相应的攻击。"
msgstr "During the exploitation stage, attackers execute malicious code to obtain system control. At this point, the Trojan has already run, and the corresponding attack can be found through antivirus software, abnormal behavior alerts, and similar methods."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:50
msgid "安装植入阶段攻击者通常会在web服务器上安装Webshell或植入后门、rootkit等来实现对服务器的持久化控制。可以通过对样本进行逆向工程来找到这些植入。"
msgstr "During the installation stage, attackers usually install WebShells on web servers or implant backdoors, rootkits, and similar components to maintain persistent control over the server. These implants can be found by reverse engineering samples."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:52
msgid "通信控制阶段攻击者已经实现了远程通信控制，木马会通过Web三方网站、DNS隧道、邮件等方式和控制服务器进行通信。此时可以通过对日志进行分析来找到木马的痕迹。"
msgstr "During the command-and-control stage, attackers have established remote communication and control. Trojans communicate with control servers through third-party Web sites, DNS tunnels, email, and similar channels. At this point, traces of the Trojan can be found through log analysis."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:54
msgid "达成目标阶段时，攻击者开始完成自己的目的，可能是破坏系统正常运行、窃取目标数据、敲诈勒索、横向移动等。此时受控机器中可能已经有攻击者的上传的攻击利用工具，此阶段可以使用蜜罐等方式来发现。"
msgstr "In the actions-on-objective stage, attackers begin to complete their goals, such as disrupting normal system operation, stealing target data, extortion, lateral movement, and similar activities. At this point, compromised machines may already contain exploitation tools uploaded by the attacker, and honeypots can be used for detection at this stage."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:57
msgid "钻石(Diamond)模型"
msgstr "Diamond Model"

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:58
msgid ""
"钻石模型由网络情报分析与威胁研究中心(The Center for Cyber Intelligence Anaysis and Threat "
"Research，CCIATR)机构的Sergio Catagirone等人在2013年提出。"
msgstr ""
"The Diamond Model was proposed in 2013 by Sergio Catagirone and others from The Center for Cyber Intelligence Anaysis and Threat "
"Research (CCIATR)."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:60
msgid "该模型把所有的安全事件(Event)分为四个核心元素，即敌手(Adversary)，能力(Capability)，基础设施(Infrastructure)和受害者(Victim)，以菱形连线代表它们之间的关系，因而命名为“钻石模型”。"
msgstr "This model divides every security Event into four core elements: Adversary, Capability, Infrastructure, and Victim. Their relationships are represented with diamond-shaped connections, hence the name Diamond Model."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:62
msgid "杀伤链模型的特点是可说明攻击线路和攻击的进程，而钻石模型的特点是可说明攻击者在单个事件中的攻击目的和所使用攻击手法。"
msgstr "The Kill Chain Model explains the attack path and attack process, while the Diamond Model explains the attacker's objective and techniques in a single event."

#: ../../source/defense/forensic.rst:64
msgid "在使用钻石模型分析时，通常使用支点分析的方式。支点(Pivoting)指提取一个元素，并利用该元素与数据源相结合以发现相关元素的分析技术。分析中可以随时变换支点，四个核心特征以及两个扩展特征(社会政治、技术)都可能成为当时的分析支点。"
msgstr "When using the Diamond Model for analysis, pivoting is commonly used. Pivoting means extracting one element and combining it with data sources to discover related elements. The pivot can be changed at any time during analysis, and the four core features plus the two extended features, socio-political and technical, can all become analysis pivots."

